news.title: Rich mainland Chinese snap up luxury homes in Singapore despite tax hikes
news.para: Mainland Chinese buyers accounted for about one-fifth of the 425 luxury units - defined as costing more than S$5 million ($3.52 million)- sold from January to August this year.

news.title: Sebi to auction properties of three companies on November 10
news.para: ​A total of ten properties of three companies will be auctioned at a reserve price totalling Rs 7.68 crore, according to a public notice issued by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi).

news.title: DPCC asked to serve show-cause notice to Parsvnath Developers over violation of norms
news.para: Delhi environment minister Gopal Rai, who was on a visit to the construction site as a part of the government's anti-dust campaign, said that the firm was found in violation of several guidelines, and was found to have kept only one anti-smog gun instead of four, that too outside the construction site.

news.title: Nashik's digital mapping to help in planning various development works
news.para: The Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) will be doing the mapping in five divisions of the civic body, covering almost 85% of the city.

news.title: Insurance platform Turtlemint leases 35,000 sq ft office near Mumbai airport
news.para: These companies have leased the space for a five-year tenure from Chalet Hotels, a K Raheja Corp company. The occupiers will be paying rentals worth around Rs 28 crore during the total term of the lease.

news.title: Nashik civic body commissioner seeks report on property tax levied on industries
news.para: The commissioner sought the report after the recent meeting with representatives of industries in which the latter had urged the civic body to reduce the property tax rates, which had been increased by the then municipal commissioner around four years ago.

news.title: Ajmera Realty & Infra India sales up 82% Rs 166 crore in Q2 FY23
news.para: The carpet area sold by ARIIL was 79,976 sq ft in Q2 FY23 which was an incremental growth of 49% from 53,801 sq ft in Q2 FY22.

news.title: Madras HC issues notice to govt over order to confer power on registrars to cancel registrations
news.para: The newly amended provision vests power on the District Registrar to adjudicate the issue whether a particular transaction is a forged one or not.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing opens public issue of bonds to raise up to Rs 800 crore
news.para: In a statement, the company said the base issue size is of Rs 100 crore with option to retain over subscription up to Rs 700 crore.

news.title: Government soon to make available 'Record of Rights' in multiple languages
news.para: A Record of Rights or RoR or jamabandi is a type of land record which captures the details of landholdings. The government now wants to address linguistic barriers in land records by translating the Record of Rights (RoR) in 22 languages.

news.title: UK house prices fall again as higher borrowing costs weigh: Halifax
news.para: House prices fell by 0.1% from August, Halifax said. In annual terms, house prices were 9.9% higher, the slowest such increase since January.

news.title: Kochi: Cherthala Infopark woos firms with rent-free period
news.para: The six-month rent-free period will be applicable to new companies that begin their operations from Cherthala campus on or before March 31, 2023, said the park authorities.

news.title: Ghaziabad civic body brings 2.4 lakh more properties under tax net
news.para: The corporation has also rolled out several concessions like rebates on house tax if the same is paid within a stipulated time. With these, the GMC hopes to generate an additional revenue of Rs 80 crore by the end of this financial year.

news.title: Fire safety: 128 buildings under Chennai development body's scanner
news.para: According to officials, the regularisation requests of these buildings were rejected by the CMDA due to inadequate particulars including fire safety norms and existence of the buildings under the regularisation scheme.

news.title: Joint development agreements must be registered: Goa RERA
news.para: RERA said that it would crack the whip on builders and real estate developers who submit only a memorandum of understanding claiming that a joint development agreement will be filed later.
